text: The 2020 United States presidential election in Illinois was held on Tuesday, November 3, 2020, as part of the 2020 United States presidential election. Former Vice President Joe Biden and his running mate U.S. Senator Kamala Harris had won 20 votes in the Electoral College. == References == Category:2020 United States presidential election Category:2020 in Illinois
title: 2020 United States presidential election in Illinois
